✅ Install Java for Web Developers and Tomcat 9
1. 🔽 Download Eclipse IDE for Enterprise Java and Web Developers
👉 Download Eclipse

Choose your OS (Windows/Linux/Mac)

Install or extract the zip folder

2. 🔽 Download and Extract Apache Tomcat 9
👉 Download Tomcat 9

Scroll to Binary Distributions

Download Core zip (e.g., apache-tomcat-9.x.xx.zip)

Extract the zip file to a known location, e.g., C:\Tomcat9

⚙️ Configure Tomcat in Eclipse
3. 🔧 Add Tomcat Server Runtime in Eclipse
Open Eclipse

Go to Window > Preferences

Navigate to Server > Runtime Environments

Click Add

Choose Apache > Tomcat v9.0 → Next

Browse to Tomcat folder (e.g., C:\Tomcat9)

Click Finish, then Apply and Close

🚀 Create and Run Your Web Project
4. 📁 Create a Dynamic Web Project
Go to File > New > Dynamic Web Project

Enter Project Name, e.g., MyServletApp

Select Target Runtime as Apache Tomcat v9.0

Keep default configuration and click Finish

5. 📝 Add Static Web Content
Navigate to:
src/main/webapp (create this folder structure if not already present)

Right-click on webapp > New > File > Name it index.html



6. 🧑‍💻 Create a Servlet
Right-click on Java Resources > src → New > Servlet

Enter:

Package name: com.example

Class name: HelloServlet

Click Finish

replace code with your java program




7. 🧪 Run Your Application
Right-click the project > Run As > Run on Server

Choose Tomcat v9.0
